    <!-- About Activity -->
    <string name="about_ui_lbl">About Serval Maps</string>
    <string name="about_ui_txt">Serval Maps is an application that supports collaborative mapping activities using a <a href="http://servalproject.org">Serval Project</a> mesh network.\n\nMap rendering is achieved using the <a href="http://mapsforge.org">mapsforge-map rendering</a> library using data sourced from <a href="http://www.openstreetmap.org">OpenStreetMap</a>. More information about OpenStreetMap licensing is <a href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">available here</a>.\n\nMore information about Serval Maps is available in the <a href="http://developer.servalproject.org/dokuwiki/doku.php?id=content:servalmaps:main_page">Serval Project Wiki</a>.</string>
    <string name="about_ui_txt_licenses">Serval Maps Copyright &#xA9; 2012 Serval Project. \n\nThis program comes with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY; for details see <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html">GPLv3</a>. This is free software, and you are welcome to redistribute it under certain conditions; for details see <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html">GPLv3</a>.\n\nThe Mapsforge library is used under the terms of the <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl.html">GNU Lesser GPL</a>.\n\nOpenStreetMap data &#xA9; <a href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/">OpenStreetMap</a> contributors, <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/">CC BY-SA</a>.\n\nPortions of the code are sourced from the Android documentation using the <a href="http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0">Apache 2.0</a> license.\n\nThe Apache Commons CSV library is used to support exporting data into CSV format, and is licensed using the <a href="http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0">Apache 2.0</a> license.\n\nThe launcher and warning icons were sourced from a free icon pack from <a href="http://www.tutorial9.net/downloads/icon-pack-256x256-business-icons/">tutorial9</a>.\n\nThe binary data format used by Serval Maps is managed using <a href="https://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/">Google Protocol Buffers</a> which is licensed using the <a href="http://code.google.com/p/protobuf/">New BSD License</a>.</string>
    
